# HermX fixture corpus manifest (Phase 0 — REFACTOR_PLAN.md:174-175, :178).
# Format: one entry per line -> "<sha256>  <relative/path/under/fixtures>"
# (compatible with `sha256sum` / `shasum -a 256` output).
#
# Scope: this manifest hash-stamps the stable INPUT corpus (alerts, strategy
# files, dry-run config, seed state, executor-output fixtures). It deliberately
# EXCLUDES:
#   * MANIFEST.sha256 itself, and
#   * snapshots/  -- the golden outputs derived by the characterization suite,
#     which are themselves the verifier for those goldens and are regenerable
#     via SNAPSHOT_UPDATE=1. Stamping them here would make every intentional
#     re-baseline look like corpus drift.
# test_fixture_manifest.py enforces this manifest and fails on any drift/missing
# file. The corpus passed the P2/S4 secret-redaction scan before commit (:176).
#
# Note: alerts/strategy/btcusdt_buy.json and btcusdt_buy_duplicate.json are
# byte-identical (same digest) BY DESIGN -- the duplicate must share the original
# dedupe identity (strategy_id|symbol|action|timeframe|tv_time).

